Package ohos.hiviewdfx

Class HiLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.hiviewdfx.HiLog

  • public final class HiLog
extends Object
    Provides methods for outputting HiLog logs.

    Before outputting logs, you must define the log type, service domain, and tag in HiLogLabel, use the interface specific to the specified log level, and specify the privacy identifier.

    Log level: debug, info, warn, error, and fatal

    Parameter format: printf format string, which starts with a % character, including a parameter type identifier and a variable parameter.

    Privacy identifier: {public} or {private} added between the % character and the parameter type identifier in each parameter.

    Example code:

    Defining a label: 

    
    static final HiLogLabel label = new HiLogLabel(HiLog.LOG_APP, MY_MODULE, "MY_TAG"); //MY_MODULE=0x00201
    Code: 
    
    HiLog.warn(label, "Failed to visit %{private}s, reason:%{public}d.", url, errno);

    Result: 05-26 11:01:06.870 1051 1051 W 00201/test: Failed to visit <private>, reason:503.

    Note: Each parameter has a privacy identifier. If no privacy identifier is added, the parameter is considered to be private.

    Since:
    1
    See Also:
    HiLogLabel
